articles.description: TRABUCO CANYON, Calif. (AP) — 4 people killed in a shooting at a Southern California biker bar, Orange County Sheriff's officials say.
articles.title: 4 people killed in a shooting at a Southern California biker bar, Orange County Sheriff's officials say

articles.description: OKUMA, Japan (AP) — The Fukushima Daiichi nuclear power plant has begun releasing its first batch of treated radioactive water into the sea.
articles.title: The Fukushima Daiichi nuclear power plant has begun releasing its first batch of treated radioactive water into the sea

articles.author: MARI YAMAGUCHI
articles.description: OKUMA, Japan (AP) — The operator of the tsunami-wrecked Fukushima Daiichi nuclear power plant says it has begun releasing its first batch of treated radioactive water into the Pacific Ocean.In a live video from a control room at the plant Thursday, Tokyo Electric Power Company Holdings showed a staff member turn on a seawater pump, marking the beginning of the controversial project that is expected to last for decades.
articles.title: The Fukushima nuclear plant begins releasing radioactive wastewater into the sea

articles.description: MILWAUKEE (AP) — Follow along for live updates on the first 2024 Republican presidential debate. The field's early front-runner, Donald Trump, skipped the event and conducted an interview with Tucker Carlson instead.
articles.title: The first 2024 Republican presidential debate is in the books. Here's what happened

articles.description: TRABUCO CANYON, Calif. (AP) — Three people have been killed in a shooting at a Southern California biker bar, Orange County Sheriff’s officials said. The shooter also died, according to authorities.
articles.title: Authorities say 4 people dead in shooting at California biker bar

articles.author: DASHA LITVINOVA
articles.description: TALLINN, Estonia (AP) — Mercenary leader Yevgeny Prigozhin, who led a brief armed rebellion against the Russian military earlier this year, was presumed dead Wednesday after a plane crash north of Moscow that killed all 10 people on board.
articles.title: Mercenary leader Yevgeny Prigozhin is presumed dead in a plane crash outside Moscow

articles.author: KATE BRUMBACK
articles.description: ATLANTA (AP) — Rudy Giuliani, Donald Trump's lawyer and confidant, turned himself in at a jail in Atlanta on Wednesday on charges related to efforts to overturn then-President Trump's loss in the 2020 presidential election in Georgia.
articles.title: Giuliani turns himself in on Georgia 2020 election charges after bond is set at $150,000

articles.author: REBECCA BOONE, HEATHER HOLLINGSWORTH, CLAUDIA LAUER and CHRISTOPHER L. KELLER
articles.description: As flames tore through a West Maui neighborhood, car after car of fleeing residents headed for the only paved road out of town in a desperate race for safety.
articles.title: In deadly Maui fires, many had no warning and no way out. Those who dodged a barricade survived

articles.author: ASHOK SHARMA and KRUTIKA PATHI
articles.description: NEW DELHI (AP) — India became the first country to land a spacecraft near the moon’s south pole on Wednesday — a historic voyage to uncharted territory that scientists believe could hold vital reserves of frozen water, and a technological triumph for the world’s most populous nation.
articles.title: India lands a spacecraft near the moon's south pole, a first for the world as it joins elite club

articles.author: JAMES POLLARD
articles.description: COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) — South Carolina’s newly all-male Supreme Court reversed course on abortion Wednesday, upholding a law banning most such procedures except in the earliest weeks of pregnancy.The continued erosion of legal abortion access across the U.S.
articles.title: South Carolina's new all-male highest court reverses course on abortion, upholding strict 6-week ban
